      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "# Release 1.1.0-beta.3\r\n\r\n\r\n##  New Features\r\n\r\n- Style inheritance on add: New columns automatically inherit the style (background, border, text color, separator, etc.) of their neighbor column. Toggleable in Settings > General > \"Inherit style on add\" (default: on).\r\n- Ctrl+Click + for opposite column type: Hold Ctrl (or Cmd on macOS) and click the + button to insert the opposite type — stacked columns get a non-stacked sibling, non-stacked columns create a new stacked group with the neighbor.\r\n- Third-party plugin autocomplete support: Column editors now bridge Obsidian's EditorSuggest API, enabling suggestions from third-party plugins (e.g. Iconize : trigger) to work inside columns.\r\n- Stack group splitting: Selecting a contiguous subset of stacked columns and toggling \"Stacked\" off now splits them into a separate stacked group instead of incorrectly nesting them.\r\n\r\n## Improvements\r\n\r\n- Default secondary background: All built-in templates (2/3/4-column, nested, sidebar, stacked+wide, Cornell notes) now use b:secondary as the default column background for better visual distinction.\r\n- Centered drag handle: The column drag handle is now a horizontal three-dot indicator (···) centered at the top of each column. On hover, it highlights with the accent color.\r\n- Context-aware + tooltip: The add column button tooltip now reflects the column context — \"Add column to the right\" for non-stacked, \"Add stacked item below\" for stacked columns.\r\n- Link color inheritance: Custom text color applied via the context menu now correctly applies to links (internal, external, tags) within the column.\r\n- Non-intrusive column header: The column header overlay no longer occupies vertical space when hidden — it only appears on hover/edit without affecting layout.\r\n\r\n## Bug Fixes\r\n\r\n- Ctrl+click conflict resolved: Ctrl+clicking the + button no longer triggers column multi-select; it correctly performs the opposite-type add action.",
